Installing Net::Disqus
    To install this module, run the following commands:

            perl Makefile.PL
            make
            make test
            make install

Disqus Data Model
    There are four types of Disqus Objects each with a corresponding Perl
    object:

  Posts -- Net::Disqus::Post
      Any comment written by a Disqus User. Each post belongs to a thread.

  Threads -- Net::Disqus::Thread
      A collection of Posts about a certian topic (A specific blog post for example).
      Each Thread Belongs to a Forum.

  Forums -- Net::Disqus::Forum
      A single website which uses Disqus. 
      
  For example: Your blog would be a Forum. Each post on your blog would have an associated Thread made up of Posts.

  Author -- Net::Disqus::Forum
      An Author which has written a post. There are two types of authors:

    * An authenticated author

    * An anonymous author

Disqus API Keys
    There are two types of API keys:

  User API Key
    Unique to each Disqus account. If a user is logged in they can find
    their "user_api_key" by visiting <http://disqus.com/api/get_my_key/>.
    You need to keep this key safe.

  Forum API Key
    Each Forum(site) has a "forum_api_key". The creator of a forum can get
    their key using the "get_forum_api_key" method call. This should be
    stored in a config file which is well protected.

API Methods
  "create_post"
    * Method -- POST

    * Key -- Forum Key

   Arguments
    * Required

      *   "thread_id" -- The ID of the thread to create the post on.

      *   "message" -- The message of the post.

      *   "author_name" -- The creator's name.

      *   "author_email" -- The creator's email address.

    * Optional

      *   "parent_post" -- The ID of the parent post, for threaded comments.

      *   "created_at" -- The time the post was created. in format:
          %Y-%m-%dT%H:%M. If ommited the current time will be used

      *   "author_url" -- The author's homepage

      *   "ip_address" -- The author's IP address

   Returns
    On success, the Net::Disqus::Post object just created.

  "get_forum_list"
    * Method -- GET

    * Key -- The user's "user_api_key"

   Arguments
    None

   Returns
    A list of "Net::Disqus::Forum objects" the user owns.

  "get_forum_api_key"
    * Method -- GET

    * Key -- The user's "user_api_key"

   Arguments
    * Required

      *   "forum_id" -- The ID of the forum being requested.

   Returns
    a string containing the forum key.

  "get_thread_list"
    * Method -- GET

    * Key -- Forum Key

    * Key -- The user's "user_api_key"

   Arguments
    None

   Returns
    A list of Net::Disqus::Thread objects belonging to the given forum.

  "get_num_posts"
    * Method -- GET

    * Key -- Forum Key

    * Key -- The user's "user_api_key"

   Arguments
    * Required

      *   "thread_ids" -- A comma delimited list of thread IDs belonging to
          the forum.

   Returns
    An pseudo object mapping each "thread_id" to two numbers: visible
    comments, total comments.

  "get_thread_by_url"
    * Method -- GET

    * Key -- Forum Key

    * Key -- The user's "user_api_key"

   Arguments
    * Required

      *   "url" -- The url to check for a thread. --TODO discover if URI
          encoded or not.

   Returns
    * On Success -- A Net::Disqus::Thread object.

    * On Failure -- NULL

  "get_thread_posts"
    * Method -- GET

    * Key -- Forum Key

    * Key -- The user's "user_api_key"

   Arguments
    * Required

      *   "thread_id" -- The ID of the thread for which you are requesting
          the posts.

   Returns
    A list of Net::Disqus::Post objects for the given thread/forum.

  "thread_by_identifier"
    * Method -- POST

    * Key -- Forum Key

    * Key -- The user's "user_api_key"

   Arguments
    * Required

      *

